JOHANNESBURG - Ratings agency Moody s says the steep decline in the country s business confidence is a setback to economic recovery.Moody s warns poor business confidence implies reduced investment, which will negatively affect growth in an already weak economy.READ: Wait for Moody's fuels uncertaintyThis will also make fiscal consolidation more challenging for the country.South African business confidence fell in the second quarter, to a level not seen since the 2009 recession.Moody's lowered South Africa's rating to the bottom of the investment grade table, with a negative outlook, earlier this month.S&P Global Ratings and Fitch currently have South Africa at junk level.eNCA